Currently the only way to get a Table of Contents macro to right-align and wrap the content around it, is to embed it in the second of two Column macros, within a Section macro. This is cumbersome because the content that you would like to place to the left of the  TOC must be entered into the first column macro, and it doesn't always split in sensible ways, eg the first column contents may be way too long, or too short, leaving too much of a gap between the text to the left of the TOC and the rest of the content.

Perhaps a property in the macro itself could align it, and wrap the text around it.

