JIRA's decorators include this line in the head of all their Sitemesh decorators:

{noformat}
<head>
    ...
    <decorator:head/>
</head>
{noformat}

This includes the <head> content (preprocessed by Sitemesh to remove content tags, etc.) from the decorated page in the output. Confluence doesn't currently do this, but it probably should to be consistent with JIRA and other Atlassian applications.

