The following directive in the AUI stylesheets causes page content to be pushed to the bottom of the page in IE8:

.aui-layout #content:before {
    content: "";
    clear: both;
    display: table;
}

This directive was in the experimental stylesheet in beta2 but in beta3 is in the "batch" css file.

If we set:

.aui-layout #content:before {
    content: none !important;
}

In our own stylesheets the problem goes away.

