Visio files should be shown in Confluence similar to other PDF and office files and to be able to *Edit in Office*

I have a simple bar chart, where the order of columns matters:

{noformat}
{chart:type=bar|stacked=true}
||expense || Jan || Feb ||
| petrol  |   0   |   2  |
| food    |   3   |   4  |
{chart}
{noformat} 
That gives us the expected graph:
!bc1.png!

But if I have a blank cell instead of '0':
{noformat}
{chart:type=bar|stacked=true}
||expense || Jan || Feb ||
| petrol  |       |   2  |
| food    |   3   |   4  |
{chart}
{noformat}

the chart macro does something odd: it interprets blank as '0', but switches the column order:

!bc2.png!

This seems buggy to me - blank is equivalent to 0 and shouldn't affect order.

----

Analysing further: it seems that only the first row matters here - eg. this works:
{noformat}
{chart:type=bar|stacked=true}
||expense || Jan || Feb ||
| petrol  |   1   |   2  |
| food    |       |   4  |
{chart}
{noformat}
!bc3.png!

I think the algorithm is looping through the first row, defining bars for columns with values, then columns at the end for columns without values:
{noformat}
{chart:type=bar|stacked=true}
||expense || Jan || Feb || Mar ||
| petrol  |       |      |  1  |
| food    |   1   |   1  |  1  |
{chart}
{noformat}
!bc4.png!

